The app does a good job of showing where everyone is at but it doesn't have any to-do actions. 

Under the two diamond charts (diamond 1 and diamond 2) should be the checklist items that the user needs to complete to level up in each skill category. 

It would also be cool if under each user's chart (diamond 1 and 2) there was a list of the four skill categories and when clicked on, it expanded to show the skill levels (1-5) and the to-do items to level up in that skill. 

There are 8 skill categories to track. 4 for diamond 1 and 4 for diamond 2. Each skill can be rated on a scale from 0 to 5. 

The diamond 1 skill categories are: Applications, Operating Systems, Customer Service, and Operations

The diamond 2 skill categories are: Security, Audio-Visual, Networks, and Project Management/Leadership

each skill sub tier should be called level 1, level 2, etc. up to level 5 and they should be displayed in a checklist that the team user can check off when they have completed that skill. The manager can see which users have completed which skills and which ones they haven't. 

It would be cool to for the manager to see progress over time on the manager dashboard. We want to do performance reviews using this data and be able to log that in the system. 

